  "title": "Electronic Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Electronic Technician </strong></p><p><strong>Job Function</strong></p><ul><li>Maintains, repairs, and installs electronic equipment used for <strong>patient care, hospital operations, and patient entertainment</strong>, including TVs, biomedical devices, and facility electronics, ensuring compliance with healthcare safety and hygiene standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Install, maintain, and troubleshoot <strong>hospital TVs and patient entertainment systems</strong></li><li>Repair and maintain <strong>medical electronic equipment</strong> (monitors, infusion pumps, diagnostic devices)</li><li>Test and service <strong>control panels, power supplies, sensors, and electronic circuits</strong></li><li>Connect and configure TVs to <strong>hospital networks, IPTV systems, or set-top boxes</strong></li><li>Perform preventive maintenance on both <strong>medical and non-medical electronics</strong></li><li>Maintain service logs, reports, and documentation for compliance and audits</li><li>Coordinate with hospital IT, nursing, and facilities teams to minimize disruption</li><li>Follow strict <strong>electrical safety and infection control procedures</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of <strong>LED/LCD/Smart TVs and AV systems</strong></li><li>Familiarity with <strong>biomedical electronic devices</strong> (optional certification can help)</li><li>Proficiency with <strong>electronic testing tools</strong> (multimeter, oscilloscope, soldering tools)</li><li>Basic networking skills for IPTV, LAN, or Wi-Fi connections</li><li>Ability to read <strong>circuit diagrams, schematics, and manuals</strong></li></ul><p>Interested applicants, please send your CV to <strong>skh_hr@stie.com.sg</strong> or apply directly via the Apply button on CareersFuture.</p>",
